snippet.textDisplay:
Love the musical duo of Ram Sampath and Sona for the kind of music they create; absolutely different element and dimension they introduce with novel artists, and bring about the taste of varied cultures of India. Absolutely creative and entertaining. Love Coke Studio absolutely to the core!

My only humble request is, and I understand this video was made 5 years ago (posting this in June 2020, BTW), that I wish they would please "TONE DOWN" the high-speed camera movement and keep it a little steady & focused on the lead artists more, so as to afford the opportunity to see and learn from them and their expressions when they belt out different notes. Also, what's up with the behind the walls & furniture objects; around, or zooming into the bright lights; or the out-of-focus camera dashing in on the artists????? 

NOT COOL at all!  

Just my two cents! But love and appreciate the work. Thank you.
